Step 1: Determine the current assets at the beginning and end of the period.  
• Beginning Current Assets (from balance sheet on 2023-12-31): 8,000,000.00  
• Ending Current Assets (from balance sheet on 2024-01-27): 9,193,203.41  

Step 2: Compute the average current assets.  
Average = (Beginning Current Assets + Ending Current Assets) / 2  
  = (8,000,000.00 + 9,193,203.41) / 2  
  = 17,193,203.41 / 2  
  ≈ 8,596,601.71  

Step 3: Retrieve the revenue from the income statement.  
Main Business Revenue = 5,565,589.48  

Step 4: Calculate the Current Assets Turnover Ratio.  
Ratio = Total Revenue / Average Current Assets  
  = 5,565,589.48 / 8,596,601.71  
  ≈ 0.647 (which rounds to about 0.65)  

Thus, the Current Assets Turnover Ratio is approximately 0.65.
